<p>GDP growth: 3.5% GDP: $729bn (PPP: $1,121bn) Inflation: 6.6% Population: 74.7m GDP per head: $9,760 (PPP: $15,000)</p>

<p>Entering its third successive term in office, the moderately Islamist Justice and Development party has the upper hand in its long-running battle with the country's secularists, but its reduced majority means that further progress on reforming the 1982 militarist constitution will have to be negotiated. The even longer-running face-off between the state and the Kurdish minority is also resurfacing, and quelling dissent before violence takes hold will be a priority. Turkey's breakneck charge out of the 2009 recession will slow, but its economy will still have some momentum.</p>

